#: unit7.rsstep6pointerspw
#, object-pascal-format
msgid "Step 6: Pointers: (PW=%s)"
msgstr "步骤 6: 指针: (密码=%s)"

#: unit7.rstryagain7
msgid "So, pointers are too difficult eh? Don't worry, try again later. For most beginners this is difficult to grasp. But I have to tell you it's a powerful feature if you learn to use it. Are you sure you want to quit?"
msgstr "所以，指针太难了是吗？别担心，以后再试。对大多数初学者来说这很难掌握。但我得告诉你，如果你学会了使用它，这是一个非常强大的功能。你确定要退出吗？"

#: unit7.rstutorialstep6
msgid ""
"Step 6: Pointers (PW = 098712)\n"
"In earlier steps you found values by scanning memory directly. This works only as long as the value stays at the same address. Many programs and games store values at different memory locations while running or each time they start. When that happens, normal scans no longer work. Pointers are used to solve this problem.\n"
"\n"
"A pointer is an address that contains another address. Even if the final value moves, the pointer usually stays the same, which allows you to always find the value again.\n"
"\n"
"At the bottom of the tutorial program there are two buttons. One button changes only the value. The other button changes both the value and the memory location. This step teaches you how to find a pointer that still works even when the location changes.\n"
"\n"
"You do not need to know assembly language for this step, but basic understanding will help.\n"
"\n"
"First, find the address of the value the same way you did in previous steps. Once you have the correct address, right-click it and choose “Find out what accesses this address.” A new window will open.\n"
"\n"
"Now click the button in the tutorial that changes the value. One or more instructions will appear in the list. It is normal to see multiple results. Some instructions write to the address, and others only read from it.\n"
"\n"
"You can double-click any instruction or select it and click “More Info” to see detailed information. Do not worry if you are unsure which instruction to use at first.\n"
"\n"
"When looking at the instructions, focus on how the memory address inside the square brackets is calculated. If an instruction does not have anything between a [ and ], ignore it and try another one.\n"
"\n"
"Both read and write instructions can be useful. Even if an instruction only reads the value, it still shows how the address was calculated. Some read instructions may also modify the register they use. This is not a problem.\n"
"\n"
"Remember that you started by telling Cheat Engine to find what accesses this specific address. That means the expression inside the square brackets must evaluate to the address of the value you found.\n"
"\n"
"For example, you might see an instruction like:\n"
"mov eax,[eax]\n"
"\n"
"This may look confusing at first. You can think of it as:\n"
"mov eax,[eax+0]\n"
"\n"
"Since you know that [eax+0] was the address you told Cheat Engine to watch, this means that the value in the EAX register before the instruction ran must have been the address of the value itself. In this case, EAX is the pointer and the offset is 0.\n"
"\n"
"The same logic applies to other instructions. Even if the instruction changes a register, you can still use the calculation inside the square brackets to determine which register holds the base pointer and what offset is used.\n"
"\n"
"If Cheat Engine’s extra information window shows what it believes the pointer value is, remember that value.\n"
"\n"
"Next, go back to the main Cheat Engine window and scan for the pointer value. Use an exact value scan in hexadecimal. If the target program is 32-bit, use a 4 byte scan. If the target program is 64-bit, pointers are usually 8 bytes, so use an 8 byte scan instead.\n"
"\n"
"After scanning, you may get one address or many addresses. In most cases, the correct pointer is the smallest address in the list.\n"
"\n"
"Now click “Add Address Manually” and enable the pointer checkbox. The window will change and allow you to enter a pointer address and an offset.\n"
"\n"
"Enter the pointer address you found. You can enter it relative to the process, for example “Tutorial-i386.exe + xxxxxx,” or you can double-click the address in the scan results to add it to the address list and then use the absolute address shown there.\n"
"\n"
"Now enter the offset. If the instruction looked like [esi+12], then the offset is 12 in hexadecimal. If it looked like [esi], then the offset is 0.\n"
"\n"
"If the instruction was more complicated, such as:\n"
"[EAX*2 + EDX + 00000310]\n"
"\n"
"Then EDX is the pointer, and everything else is part of the offset. For example, if eax was 4C, the offset would be calculated as 2 times 4C plus 310, which equals 3A8 in hexadecimal. You can use Windows Calculator in Programmer mode to do hexadecimal calculations.\n"
"\n"
"Click OK to add the pointer. If everything was done correctly, the address in the list will show something like P->xxxxxxx, where xxxxxxx is the actual address of the value. If it does not, then something went wrong in an earlier step.\n"
"\n"
"Finally, use the pointer you added to change the value to 5000 and check the Active box to freeze it. Then click the Change Pointer button in the tutorial. If the pointer works correctly, the Next button will appear.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"As an extra option, you can also use Cheat Engine’s pointer scanner to automatically search for pointers. This is especially useful in real games, but it is slower and more advanced."
msgstr ""
"步骤 6：指针 (密码 = 098712)\n"
"在之前的步骤中，你通过直接扫描内存来找到值。这只在值保持在同一地址时有效。许多程序和游戏在运行时或每次启动时会将值存储在不同的内存位置。当这种情况发生时，普通扫描不再起作用。指针就是用来解决这个问题的。\n"
"\n"
"指针是一个包含另一个地址的地址。即使最终值移动了，指针通常保持不变，这让你可以始终再次找到该值。\n"
"\n"
"在教程程序底部有两个按钮。一个按钮只改变值。另一个按钮同时改变值和内存位置。这一步教你如何找到一个即使位置改变仍然有效的指针。\n"
"\n"
"这一步你不需要了解汇编语言，但基本的理解会有所帮助。\n"
"\n"
"首先，用和之前步骤相同的方式找到值的地址。一旦你有了正确的地址，右键点击它并选择 \"查找访问此地址的代码\"。一个新窗口将打开。\n"
"\n"
"现在点击教程中改变值的按钮。列表中将出现一个或多个指令。看到多个结果是正常的。有些指令写入地址，有些只读取。\n"
"\n"
"你可以双击任何指令或选中它并点击 \"更多信息\" 来查看详细信息。如果你一开始不确定用哪个指令也没关系。\n"
"\n"
"查看指令时，关注方括号内的内存地址是如何计算的。如果一条指令在 [ 和 ] 之间没有任何内容，忽略它并尝试另一个。\n"
"\n"
"读取和写入指令都可能有用。即使一条指令只读取值，它仍然显示了地址是如何计算的。一些读取指令可能也会修改它们使用的寄存器。这不是问题。\n"
"\n"
"记住，你一开始是让 Cheat Engine 查找访问这个特定地址的代码。这意味着方括号内的表达式必须计算为你找到的值的地址。\n"
"\n"
"例如，你可能会看到这样的指令：\n"
"mov eax,[eax]\n"
"\n"
"这乍一看可能令人困惑。你可以把它想成：\n"
"mov eax,[eax+0]\n"
"\n"
"既然你知道 [eax+0] 是你让 Cheat Engine 监视的地址，这意味着在指令运行前 EAX 寄存器中的值必须是值本身的地址。在这种情况下，EAX 就是指针，偏移量为 0。\n"
"\n"
"同样的逻辑适用于其他指令。即使指令改变了寄存器，你仍然可以使用方括号内的计算来确定哪个寄存器持有基址指针以及使用了什么偏移量。\n"
"\n"
"如果 Cheat Engine 的额外信息窗口显示了它认为的指针值，记住那个值。\n"
"\n"
"接下来，回到 Cheat Engine 主窗口并扫描指针值。使用十六进制精确值扫描。如果目标程序是 32 位的，使用 4 字节扫描。如果目标程序是 64 位的，指针通常是 8 字节，所以改用 8 字节扫描。\n"
"\n"
"扫描后，你可能得到一个地址或多个地址。在大多数情况下，正确的指针是列表中最小的地址。\n"
"\n"
"现在点击 \"手动添加地址\" 并启用指针复选框。窗口将改变，允许你输入指针地址和偏移量。\n"
"\n"
"输入你找到的指针地址。你可以输入相对于进程的地址，例如 \"Tutorial-i386.exe + xxxxxx\"，或者你可以双击扫描结果中的地址将其添加到地址列表，然后使用那里显示的绝对地址。\n"
"\n"
"现在输入偏移量。如果指令看起来像 [esi+12]，那么偏移量是十六进制的 12。如果看起来像 [esi]，那么偏移量是 0。\n"
"\n"
"如果指令更复杂，例如：\n"
"[EAX*2 + EDX + 00000310]\n"
"\n"
"那么 EDX 是指针，其他所有都是偏移量的一部分。例如，如果 eax 是 4C，偏移量将计算为 2 乘以 4C 加上 310，等于十六进制的 3A8。你可以使用 Windows 计算器的程序员模式进行十六进制计算。\n"
"\n"
"点击确定添加指针。如果一切正确，列表中的地址将显示类似 P->xxxxxxx，其中 xxxxxxx 是值的实际地址。如果不是这样，那么在之前的某个步骤出了问题。\n"
"\n"
"最后，使用你添加的指针将值改为 5000 并勾选激活框来冻结它。然后点击教程中的改变指针按钮。如果指针工作正确，下一步按钮将出现。\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"作为额外选项，你也可以使用 Cheat Engine 的指针扫描器自动搜索指针。这在真实游戏中特别有用，但它更慢也更高级。"

